spans.text: She tunes my easy rhyme and gives the lay to flow
with what a careless grace she flings Her artful hand across the sounding strings
sleep she seem to close Her languid lids
her repose With lulling notes , and thousand beauties
me raise My feeble voice to sound the victor's praise , To paint the hero's toil
the vaulted skies loud Ios rend , In golden chains should loaded monarchs bend , And hoary Nile with pensive aspect
the glories of his sevenfold stream
tell of Jove and Phlegra's blasted plain
the tale of Troy for Helen's sake
that can my captive heart release And to this bosom give its wonted peace
while over the place you drop a tear , Love and the fair were of his life the pride ; He lived while she was kind , and , when she frowned , he died
